=\"#feedbackModal_main_2529429\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 09, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104kxz1665702893355.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kxz1665702893355.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kxz1665702893355.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"kxz1665702893355\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Data Type Mapping Between Uniface and Java\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"kxz1665702893355__data_type_mapping_between_uniface_and_java_115276\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Data type conversions are all handled by Uniface and the\n         <span class=\"ph filepath\">Uniface*.class</span> files included in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">ujci30.jar</span>\n      file. </p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Default Data Type Mappings Between Uniface and Java</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__1\">\nProcScript data\ntype\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__2\">\nDefault\nJava data type\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__3\">\nRemarks\n</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">String</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">String</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__3\">\nJava\nuses unicode\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Numeric</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">int</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__3\">\nLimited\nto Java capacity\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Float</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">double</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__3\">\nLimited\nto Java capacity\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Boolean</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">boolean</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__3\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Date</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">UnifaceDateTime</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__3\">\nA Uniface\nclass\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Time</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">UnifaceDateTime</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__3\">\nA Uniface\nclass\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Datetime</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">UnifaceDateTime</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__3\">\nA Uniface\nclass\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Entity</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">UnifaceEntity</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__3\">\nA Uniface\nclass\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Raw</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__2\">array of <code class=\"ph codeph\">byte</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__3\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Occurrence</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">UnifaceOccurrence</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__3\">\nA Uniface\nclass\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Image</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">java.awt.Image</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1__entry__3\"></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kxz1665702893355__p_d35873e1_d35874e1_d35875e1\">The following Uniface data types are not currently supported for Java:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"kxz1665702893355__li_d18308e1_d18309e1_d18310e1\">Linear Date\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"kxz1665702893355__li_d18311e1_d18312e1_d18313e1\">Linear Time\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"kxz1665702893355__li_d18314e1_d18315e1_d18316e1\">Linear Datetime\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kxz1665702893355__p_d35876e1_d35877e1_d35878e1\">The following table lists Uniface to Java data type mappings that differ from the default types, when Java-specific signature information is available:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3623e1_d3624e1_d3625e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">Other Data Type Mappings Between Uniface and Java</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3623e1_d3624e1_d3625e1__entry__1\"> ProcScript data type </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3623e1_d3624e1_d3625e1__entry__2\"> Java data types </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3623e1_d3624e1_d3625e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">String </code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3623e1_d3624e1_d3625e1__entry__2\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">char</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">Character</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">String\n                     </code>(Default) </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3623e1_d3624e1_d3625e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Numeric </code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3623e1_d3624e1_d3625e1__entry__2\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">byte</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">Byte</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">short</code>,\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">Short</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">int </code>(Default),\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">Integer</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">long</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">Long</code>,\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">String </code>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3623e1_d3624e1_d3625e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Float </code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3623e1_d3624e1_d3625e1__entry__2\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">float</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">Float</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">double\n                     </code>(Default), <code class=\"ph codeph\">Double</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">String </code>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3623e1_d3624e1_d3625e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Boolean </code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kxz1665702893355__table_d3623e1_d3624e1_d3625e1__entry__2\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">boolean </code>(Default), <code class=\"ph codeph\">Boolean </code>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kxz1665702893355__topic_d23472e1_d23473e1_d23474e1_d23475e1_d23476e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d552213e516\">\n                        \n Image Data Type\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kxz1665702893355__p_d35882e1_d35883e1_d35884e1\">The Image data type allows image conversion to Java image types from more types than are supported by version 1.3 of the JDK, which only supports <span class=\"ph filepath\">.gif</span> and <span class=\"ph filepath\">.jpeg</span> image types. Uniface only supports conversion from Uniface to Java. Conversions from Java to Uniface can only be done as binary data, <span class=\"ph filepath\">.gif</span> data, for example.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kxz1665702893355__p_d35885e1_d35886e1_d35887e1\">If the image is a <span class=\"ph filepath\">.gif</span> or <span class=\"ph filepath\">.jpeg</span>, it is more efficient to use the <code class=\"ph codeph\">createImage()</code> or <code class=\"ph codeph\">getImage()</code> methods from the Java Abstract Windows Toolkit (AWT) to convert to a Java image, because the extra Uniface to Java image format conversions are bypassed.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kxz1665702893355__p_d35888e1_d35889e1_d35890e1\">If an image cannot be converted, due to an unrecognized format or null data, then a null pointer is returned. No exception is thrown.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"kxz1665702893355__note_w5828ab1b5c13b9_w5829ab1b5c13_w5830ab1b5_w5831ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> One image can contain more than one picture. Uniface can convert only single pictures. This also applies to icons which have extra background pictures.</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529429\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529429\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Data Type Mapping Between Uniface and Java Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Data Type Mapping Between Uniface and Java Data type conversions are all handled by Uniface and the Uniface*.class files included in the ujci30.jar file. Table 1. Default Data Type Mappings Between Uniface and Java ProcScript data type Default Java data type Remarks String String Java uses unicode Numeric int Limited to Java capacity Float double Limited to Java capacity Boolean boolean Date UnifaceDateTime A Uniface class Time UnifaceDateTime A Uniface class Datetime UnifaceDateTime A Uniface class Entity UnifaceEntity A Uniface class Raw array of byte Occurrence UnifaceOccurrence A Uniface class Image java.awt.Image The following Uniface data types are not currently supported for Java: Linear Date Linear Time Linear Datetime The following table lists Uniface to Java data type mappings that differ from the default types, when Java-specific signature information is available: Table 2. Other Data Type Mappings Between Uniface and Java ProcScript data type Java data types String char , Character , String (Default) Numeric byte , Byte , short , Short , int (Default), Integer , long , Long , String Float float , Float , double (Default), Double , String Boolean boolean (Default), Boolean Image Data Type The Image data type allows image conversion to Java image types from more types than are supported by version 1.3 of the JDK, which only supports .gif and .jpeg image types. Uniface only supports conversion from Uniface to Java. Conversions from Java to Uniface can only be done as binary data, .gif data, for example. If the image is a .gif or .jpeg , it is more efficient to use the createImage() or getImage() methods from the Java Abstract Windows Toolkit (AWT) to convert to a Java image, because the extra Uniface to Java image format conversions are bypassed. If an image cannot be converted, due to an unrecognized format or null data, then a null pointer is returned. No exception is thrown. Note: One image can contain more than one picture. Uniface can convert only single pictures. This also applies to icons which have extra background pictures. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}